<title>USA: Granite Finl Q3 March 31 profit vs loss.</title>
<headline>Granite Finl Q3 March 31 profit vs loss.</headline>
<dateline>WESTMINSTER, Colo. 1997-05-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>GRANITE FINANCIAL INC</p>
<p>				Three Months Ended  Nine Months Ended</p>
<p>				     Pro forma  Pro forma   Pro forma</p>
<p>				    Mar 31,   Mar 31, Mar 31, Mar 31,</p>
<p>					 1997	1996    1997    1996</p>
<p> Revenues			 $23,460    $4,012 $53,226 $16,514</p>
<p>Costs</p>
<p>   Cost of leases sold	 20,865     3,650  46,876  15,296</p>
<p>   Provision for credit losses  312	  45     443	47</p>
<p>   Interest expense		 436	  17   1,377	18</p>
<p>Securitization expenses</p>
<p>    and amortization		114	 ---     257     ---</p>
<p>	  Total costs	    21,727     3,712  48,953  15,361</p>
<p> Gross profit		     1,733	 300   4,273   1,153</p>
<p> SG&amp;A				   826	 310   1,935     789</p>
<p> Income (loss) before taxes     907	(10)   2,338     364</p>
<p> Income taxes expense (credit)  353	 (4)     983     134</p>
<p> Net income (loss)		  554	 (6)   1,355     230</p>
<p> Earnings per share		0.14	 ---    0.44    0.11</p>
<p> Wgtd avg shrs		    3,858     2,000   3,094   2,000</p>
<p>			(Thousands, Except Per Share Data)</p>
<p>Note: Effective October 1996, Granite Financial Inc became the successor company to Granite Financial LLC a limited liability company that had not been subject to federal and state income taxes.</p>
<p>Pro forma net income (loss) information shown assumes income taxes had been provided for at statutory rates.</p>
<p>In accordance with generally accepted accounting principles the company recorded a $100,000 one-time charge against earnings during October, 1996, for income taxes associated with the Company's restructuring.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610</p>
